TY  - JOUR
T1  - Some Stochastic Inventory Models for Rental Situations
AU  - Tainiter, M.
Y1  - 1964/11/01
PY  - 1964
DA  - 1964/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.11.2.316
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.11.2.316
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 316
EP  - 326
VL  - 11
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Some stochastic models are analyzed which describe the time fluctuations of the inventory levels of companies which are in the rental business. The stochastic process which describes the fluctuations is shown to be applicable to a wide variety of physical situations. Examples are given, and analyses are made of several types of profit functions which are applicable to rental situations.
AB  - Some stochastic models are analyzed which describe the time fluctuations of the inventory levels of companies which are in the rental business. The stochastic process which describes the fluctuations is shown to be applicable to a wide variety of physical situations. Examples are given, and analyses are made of several types of profit functions which are applicable to rental situations.
